&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Position Summary&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a Senior Management Accountant to join our team who has the capability and desire to grow into a Finance Manager. This role will act as a right hand to our Group FP&amp;amp;A Manager and will be required to step into high-level meetings on behalf of the FP&amp;amp;A Manager. This is a unique opportunity for someone hungry and passionate to grow not only in their own role, but also provide key input to help grow the entire Finance department as Bitfury scales.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Duties and responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own the Month End process – Facilitate and complete monthly close procedures to agreed timeline and consolidation of the group for reporting.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Analyze and review financial reports on a monthly and quarterly basis which will be distributed to our shareholders.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work closely with key stakeholders in the business to help them understand their departmental financial figures and identify areas where costs can be controlled.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Tracking financial performance, including identifying and providing commentary on the drivers of variances between actual, budgeted and forecasted performance.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design, development, and maintenance of robust FP&amp;amp;A reports to support regular communication to the Board and Executive team on financial performance and trends.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build relationships within the business with a view to improve overall cost-base efficiencies and enable effective decision making&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Liaise with key Head of functions in the business to discuss, prepare and manage the budget for each business unit.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deliver consistent, timely, accurate, high quality, and insightful financial and non-financial materials to facilitate and support commercial decision making.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work closely with the systems team to maintain and enhance our financial tools.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Leverage your experience to continuously improve our systems, procedures and processes within the Finance department to ensure operational excellence.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Broader support of finance team and ad-hoc projects including collection, analysis, and management of data to provide analytical insights.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ideally, university educated with accountancy qualification (ACA/ACCA) or equivalent&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ideally worked with NetSuite and financial planning tools (PBCS, OneStream etc.)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience in providing actionable insights to support commercial decision making&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Able to combine a confidence to challenge and assert one’s own views amongst senior colleagues and peers with an ability to listen, influence, and adapt to the viewpoints and opinions of others&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Enjoys working in a hands-on environment and has a genuine interest in understanding the numbers&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Able to tackle complex problems in an environment of ambiguity where not all the desired information may be available&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Advanced user of excel, with excellent skills in financial modelling and trend analysis&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Public listed company experience desired&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong sense of ownership and accountability&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Personal traits and characteristics&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Curious, well-organized, capable of meeting multiple deliverables in strict deadlines, a self-start team worker who works well under pressure, he/she will be enthusiastic in looking for improvements and be prepared to challenge the existing thinking and practices. He/she will be comfortable working in a multi-cultural environment and be flexible and adoptable to achieve targets.&lt;/p&gt;
